  <TestInformation>
    <Title>Rise of the Tomb Raider</Title>
    <Description>Rise of the Tomb Raider on Steam.

The test profile assumes you have a Steam account, have Steam installed for the system, and that you own a copy of this game. This automates the process of executing the game and using its built-in benchmark mode.

Backs up old preferences (in ~/.local/share/feral-interactive/) for the run.

NOTES for cross-platform comparisons:
    Due to the extreme demands of "Very High" 4K Texture Detail on all platforms, which can need ~6GB+ of VRAM, the "Very High" graphics preset on Linux only sets Texture Detail to "High".
    Nvidia ambient occlusion modes are not featured on the Linux version (HBAO+ and VXAO).

See notes in install.sh for a few small tweaks including disabling the CPU governor check when testing for it's effects
    </Description>
